<%@ page language="java" contentType="text/html; charset=UTF-8"
	pageEncoding="UTF-8"%>
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<title>로그인</title>
<link rel="stylesheet" href="mainpage.css">
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
</head>
<body>
	<form action="LoginServlet" method="post">
		<%
		// Check if the user is logged in by verifying the session attributes
		String loggedIn = (String) session.getAttribute("user_id");
		String userName = (String) session.getAttribute("user_name");

		// If logged in, show the user's name as non-clickable text; otherwise, show the login link
		if (loggedIn != null && !loggedIn.isEmpty()) {
		%>
		<header>
			<h1>Main Page</h1>
			<div class="navbar">
				<ul>
					<li class="active"><a href="website.jsp">TOP 여행지</a></li>
					<li class="mainpage-name"><span><%=userName%>님</span></li>
				</ul>
			</div>
			<div class="title">
				<h1>Main Page</h1>
			</div>
			<div class="button">
				<a href="#" class="btn">LEARN MORE</a>
			</div>
		</header>
		<%
		} else {
		%>
		<header>
			<h1>Main Page</h1>
			<div class="navbar">
				<ul>
					<li class="active"><a href="website.jsp">TOP 여행지</a></li>
					<li><a href="login.jsp">로그인</a></li>
				</ul>
			</div>
			<div class="title">
				<h1>Main Page</h1>
			</div>
			<div class="button">
				<a href="#" class="btn">LEARN MORE</a>
			</div>
		</header>
		<%
		}
		%>
		In this modification, the <a> tag for the user's name has been
			replaced with a <span> tag. This change will render the
				username as non-clickable text, preventing any hyperlink
				functionality. The username will be displayed in the same position
				but without the hyperlink. Update your website.jsp with this
				adjusted code to ensure that the username is displayed as
				non-clickable text once a user is logged in. 
	</form>
</body>
</html>